81
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,130
I don't want cereal.

82
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:24,360
I guess I should give rita back her key.

83
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:33,730
Cody,no. No,let mommy get the d--

84
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,730
it's Dexter!

85
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,130
He brought doughnuts!

86
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:39,700
I did. I also brought... A dragon zombie!

87
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:41,500
I knew you'd find it!

88
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:45,560
Hope it's okay I'm here.

89
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:48,660
Could you watch them while I finish getting ready?

90
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,760
Astor still has homework.

91
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:01,660
Thank you,Dexter.

92
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,730
Meet me at the car.

93
00:06:06,430 --> 00:06:09,160
Good thing I dropped by.

94
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,860
Don't ever do it again.

95
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:13,930
I'm sorry?

96
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:16,660
It's too hard on the kids,and it's too hard on me.

97
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:18,530
It's paul all over again.

98
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:22,100
Please,Dexter,just stay away.

99
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,500
You'll notice we have some new faces here.

100
00:06:33,530 --> 00:06:34,830
Please make them feel welcome.

101
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:38,560
Our immediate task is to re-examine every criminal case

102
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,260
involving our 18 victims.

103
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,800
Where would you like us to start?

104
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:43,430
By answering every question

105
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:45,860
as honestly and with as much detail as you can.

106
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:48,960
Excuse me,sir. Answering questions?

107
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,360
That is correct.

108
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,130
I can hardly expect you to investigate your own cases.

109
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:57,260
What are you saying? Are we under investigation?

110
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:59,060
We are now operating under the assumption

111
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:01,430
that our killer is somehow connected to law enforcement.

112
00:07:01,460 --> 00:07:04,360
Whether he be a file clerk,a dispatch officer,

113
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,560
park ranger... Or a police officer.

114
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,530
Or a police officer.

115
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:11,030
Is that why you brought in all these suits?

116
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:12,400
Special agents.

117
00:07:12,430 --> 00:07:15,000
Sir,you risk alienating every cop on the task force

118
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,460
if you do this.

119
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:19,230
We go where the chase leads us...

120
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:22,160
Even if it gets messy.

121
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,430
It's insulting.

122
00:07:28,460 --> 00:07:30,500
We're just as capable as they are

123
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:32,400
of looking into our own cases.

124
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:34,760
Who wears a wool suit in the middle of summer in miami?

125
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,160
Nazis -- that's who. It's all about intimidation.

126
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,560
And the idea that one of us could be the killer?

127
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,760
It's complete bullshit.

128
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:43,900
What do you mean? "Us" who?

129
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:46,730
Lundy has his feds investigating all of our cases

130
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,800
that are tied to the bay harbor victims.

131
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:50,260
That's good here.

132
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:53,330
Look,we got to stand tough here.

133
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,060
We got to make it clear to them

134
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,400
that we're not gonna be

135
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:58,430
their little "yes,sir,no,sir" lapdogs.

136
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:02,130
Gentlemen.

137
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:05,430
Morgan,I'd like to go over some of your cases tomorrow.

138
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:06,930
Got them all listed right there.

139
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,760
It would be helpful if you could gather up

140
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,660
any notes you may have taken.

141
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,100
Happy to help.

142
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:17,930
Way to stand tough,Dexter.

143
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,060
Sorry.

144
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,900
That's exactly how hitler walked.

145
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:27,660
It seems my manifesto

146
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:30,630
unintentionally helped lundy narrow his focus.

147
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:33,430
That's what I get for trying to emulate lila

148
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,930
and take the offensive.

149
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:37,530
I've always worked best in the shadows,

150
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:39,760
and that's where I have to stay.

151
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,200
Lundy's really pissing people off.

152
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:45,930
He's got his whole crew looking through every case

153
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:48,360
involving any of the bay harbor victims.

154
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,960
He sounds desperate.

155
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,030
You know you're gonna be called in.

156
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:54,600
I'll be curious to see if I show up.

157
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:58,400
Okay,james,you need to be a little careful here.

158
00:08:58,430 --> 00:09:01,130
If you want to keep your job,you got to cooperate.

159
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,900
Being on suspension does not exclude you from this.

160
00:09:03,930 --> 00:09:05,860
And who was it that suspended me again?

161
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,260
Oh,shit. That was you.

162
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:10,200
Please,don't act like you didn't deserve it.

163
00:09:10,230 --> 00:09:12,300
Your case is coming up for review in a week.

164
00:09:12,330 --> 00:09:13,900
If you want to keep your job --

165
00:09:13,930 --> 00:09:15,360
you keep saying that,maria.

166
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,460
What makes you think I want to keep my job?

167
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:20,860
Are you just talking here,

168
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:23,830
or is this something that you've seriously considered?

169
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:25,330
Well,you and I both know

170
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:28,030
that I have gone as high as I can over there.

171
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:30,760
Maybe it's time to move on.

172
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,500
Well,what would you do?

173
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:36,600
I don't know. My father was a butcher.

174
00:09:36,630 --> 00:09:38,630
Maybe I'll open up my own butcher shop.

175
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:42,200
Yeah, I can just see you putting on an apron every morning.

176
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:46,400
Look, I have a friend.

177
00:09:46,430 --> 00:09:49,230
He's the head of personnel at stillwater security.

178
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:50,600
Government contractors?

179
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:53,100
They're always looking for people like you.

180
00:09:53,130 --> 00:09:54,630
It's a dangerous world out there.

181
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:56,800
They pay a lot of money to make it safe.

182
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:58,460
Yeah,you got that right.

183
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:02,600
All right. Set it up. I'll meet with your guy.

184
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:05,460
Officer morgan. Debra.

185
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,030
Yes?

186
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:10,230
I picked the rodrigo case for you to look into --

187
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:12,000
small-time dope dealer.

188
00:10:12,030 --> 00:10:15,260
Arrested for murder,ended up walking free,

189
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:17,160
then disappeared off the face of the earth

190
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,900
until his body was found in a garbage bag in the ocean.

191
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:24,130
Not exciting enough for you?

192
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:26,600
Well,it's just...I'm homicide.

193
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:28,530
I mean, I thought you didn't want us

194
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,230
checking into our own cases.

195
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:31,600
You're new to homicide.

196
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:33,800
At the time of this case,you were still in vice.

197
00:10:33,830 --> 00:10:35,600
No conflict there.

198
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:38,860
Well,I'm flattered you want me in on this,but...

199
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:41,100
Batista and doakes were lead here.

200
00:10:41,130 --> 00:10:44,600
I feel kind of weird about investigating my own colleagues.

201
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:46,400
Weird. Gosh.

202
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:48,900
I'd hate for you to feel weird.

203
00:10:48,930 --> 00:10:51,300
You know what I mean.

204
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:58,860
Would you have dinner with me tomorrow night?

205
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:02,100
Or would that make you feel weird?

206
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:07,530
I'd love to have dinner with you.

207
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:09,400
Good.

208
00:11:09,430 --> 00:11:11,900
I'll take you to the best restaurant in miami.

209
00:11:11,930 --> 00:11:14,530
Wow. Great.

210
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:33,160
I like the smell. Don't you?

211
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,360
Like something exciting happened here.

212
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,800
It's like when a piece of bread gets stuck in the toaster.

213
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:42,730
You like to pretend there's no poetry in you.

214
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:45,060
So,what's the problem with the insurance company?

215
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,700
Why aren't they paying?

216
00:11:47,730 --> 00:11:49,030
It's ridiculous.

217
00:11:49,060 --> 00:11:53,030
They think the fire is of suspicious origin,

218
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:55,960
and they need to finish their investigation.

219
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,360
What do they mean,"suspicious"?

220
00:11:57,400 --> 00:12:00,030
Are they saying you started the fire on purpose?

221
00:12:00,060 --> 00:12:02,360
Who knows what they're saying?

222
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,900
You know insurance companies --

223
00:12:03,930 --> 00:12:06,760
anything to keep from paying out.

224
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:17,760
Yeah,especially when a fire  has multiple points of origin.

225
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:22,200
So,you never told me.

226
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:26,130
How did it go at rita's this morning?

227
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:29,030
Uh,you know, I just returned cody's toy,

228
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:30,900
and that was it.

229
00:12:30,930 --> 00:12:33,360
No quickie on the kitchen table?

230
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,600
Rita doesn't have a kitchen table.

231
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:38,730
Oh,clever way of not answering the question.

232
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:41,260
It was...

233
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,900
Awkward,actually.

234
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:46,460
Always is.

235
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:49,630
You can't go back. You know that.

236
00:12:49,660 --> 00:12:51,700
I'm not trying to go anywhere.

237
00:12:51,730 --> 00:12:54,930
Well,the bed's all ready.

238
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,830
Uh, I can't.

239
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:00,000
And why would that be?

240
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:01,300
I have too much work to do.

241
00:13:03,030 --> 00:13:06,100
I have all these case files I have to go over for tomorrow.

242
00:13:06,130 --> 00:13:08,300
You didn't bring any work with you?

243
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:12,960
Home. I need to...Work at home.

244
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:15,360
Okay.

245
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,630
Goodbye,then.

246
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:19,430
So,I'll see you tomorrow?

247
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,760
Whatever.

248
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:43,200
Is it possible she started  that fire on purpose?

249
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:44,760
I can't imagine why.

250
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:48,600
What I do know is that I can't  take any risks right now.

251
00:14:03,530 --> 00:14:04,900
Hi,you wanted to --

252
00:14:04,930 --> 00:14:07,160
morgan,come in.

253
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,760
Can I offer you some tea?

254
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,500
Uh,no,thank you. I'm...

255
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:14,230
And he pours it anyway.

256
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:16,360
He's trying to throw me  off balance,

257
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:20,430
show that I don't have  the power to say no to him.

258
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:22,560
How about some sesame crackers to go with that?

259
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,060
So I'll say yes to everything.

260
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:25,200
I'd love some.

261
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:31,300
Oh. Sorry. Guess I ate them all.

262
00:14:31,330 --> 00:14:33,160
Asshole.

263
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:39,300
So,you worked firsthand on,

264
00:14:39,330 --> 00:14:41,000
what,four of the cases

265
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:43,700
related to the bay harbor investigation?

266
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:45,660
I believe so.

267
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:48,400
Your reports were a real pleasure to read.

268
00:14:50,060 --> 00:14:53,800
Concise,meticulous. I appreciate that.

