617
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:03,660
"March 17th -- airplane flying too low."

618
00:34:03,700 --> 00:34:06,200
I told you,this guy's a fruit bat.

619
00:34:06,230 --> 00:34:10,460
"April." Hey,it's the month we want.

620
00:34:12,130 --> 00:34:15,200
"April 16th"...

621
00:34:15,230 --> 00:34:17,560
Fuck me sideways,listen to this.

622
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,660
"Rodrigo gets into car parked in wrong space.

623
00:34:19,700 --> 00:34:21,800
Must be drunk because someone is carrying him."

624
00:34:21,830 --> 00:34:23,330
The license plate's right here.

625
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,300
This is from 9:00 the night he disappeared.

626
00:34:25,330 --> 00:34:26,800
The last time anyone saw him alive.

627
00:34:26,830 --> 00:34:27,960
We got to run that plate.

628
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:29,900
I bet whoever owned this fucking car is our killer.

629
00:34:29,930 --> 00:34:31,060
I'm gonna get lundy.

630
00:34:31,100 --> 00:34:32,230
He's out with his feds.

631
00:34:32,260 --> 00:34:33,830
Well,I'm calling him in.

632
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:44,730
Lila almost had me believing  it was possible to change,

633
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:47,500
to become something else,

634
00:34:47,530 --> 00:34:50,460
as if that ever really happens.

635
00:34:50,500 --> 00:34:54,400
I've always known what I am.

636
00:34:54,430 --> 00:34:56,700
If the glove fits...

637
00:36:23,700 --> 00:36:28,230
A secret cabin in the middle  of the everglades --

638
00:36:28,260 --> 00:36:32,400
what more could a rededicated  serial killer ask for?

639
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:47,260
Cocaine.

640
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:50,730
Apparently mr. Jiminez never  gave up his old habits.

641
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:54,000
What a bad,bad man.

642
00:37:24,330 --> 00:37:27,700
What? You think it just turned on by itself?

643
00:37:30,700 --> 00:37:33,800
"Ugh,there is no such plate."

644
00:37:33,830 --> 00:37:36,460
Is that a 1 or an "i"? Fuck you,lenny.

645
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:38,400
Fuck your handwriting.

646
00:37:43,600 --> 00:37:45,300
Debra.

647
00:37:45,330 --> 00:37:46,960
Kind of busy here.

648
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,400
Then can you please tell me where I can find Dexter?

649
00:37:50,430 --> 00:37:52,130
I brought him some dinner.

650
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:53,660
Dexter's not here.

651
00:37:53,700 --> 00:37:54,800
Where is he?

652
00:37:54,830 --> 00:37:56,060
How should I know?

653
00:37:56,100 --> 00:37:58,130
He said he was working late.

654
00:37:59,930 --> 00:38:02,260
Is that what he told you?

655
00:38:02,300 --> 00:38:04,430
What do you mean?

656
00:38:04,460 --> 00:38:06,930
He's not working late.

657
00:38:08,430 --> 00:38:11,030
I think he lied to you.

658
00:38:11,060 --> 00:38:13,060
Oh,men are such pigs.

659
00:38:23,730 --> 00:38:26,260
I'm so sorry. I'm sure he'll show up.

660
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:28,630
He's very excited about this job.

661
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:04,100
I swear,I have tried every combination.

662
00:39:04,130 --> 00:39:06,600
Nothing is coming up.

663
00:39:06,630 --> 00:39:09,560
I told you lenny would be a waste of time.

664
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:11,800
Maybe it's not a florida plate.

665
00:39:14,830 --> 00:39:17,630
Try georgia.

666
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:20,200
Holy shit,here it is.

667
00:39:20,230 --> 00:39:23,700
The vehicle was registered to charlie lewis.

668
00:39:23,730 --> 00:39:25,630
I know that name.

669
00:39:25,660 --> 00:39:28,500
A drug dealer out of new york.

670
00:39:28,530 --> 00:39:30,200
A tough guy --

671
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:32,100
likes to carry a big-ass knife.

672
00:39:32,130 --> 00:39:34,530
That's our guy. That's the bay harbor butcher.

673
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:37,800
I told you he wasn't a cop.

674
00:39:37,830 --> 00:39:39,900
What?

675
00:39:39,930 --> 00:39:41,300
Shit.

676
00:39:41,330 --> 00:39:43,530
Where is he?

677
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:46,500
According to this,south bay correctional facility.

678
00:39:46,530 --> 00:39:47,730
For how long?

679
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,900
Oh,shit.

680
00:39:49,930 --> 00:39:53,360
Charlie lewis was arrested april 12,2002.

681
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,130
That's four days before rodrigo was seen

682
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:56,760
being carried into the car.

683
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:58,430
Who had his car? One of his gang?

684
00:39:58,460 --> 00:40:00,100
This is where it gets really bad.

685
00:40:00,130 --> 00:40:01,830
The vehicle was seized as evidence.

686
00:40:01,860 --> 00:40:03,300
By who?

687
00:40:03,330 --> 00:40:05,430
By our department.

688
00:40:05,460 --> 00:40:08,100
Where was the vehicle held?

689
00:40:08,130 --> 00:40:11,260
Right here in our evidence lab,behind a secure gate.

690
00:40:11,300 --> 00:40:14,300
Someone signed the vehicle out,picked rodrigo up,

691
00:40:14,330 --> 00:40:16,660
killed him,and then signed the vehicle back in.

692
00:40:16,700 --> 00:40:18,200
So you have records.

693
00:40:18,230 --> 00:40:19,900
Why would we keep them?

694
00:40:19,930 --> 00:40:22,260
The only people allowed access to those vehicles

695
00:40:22,300 --> 00:40:24,860
are members of the miami metro police department.

696
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:26,500
Holy shit.

697
00:40:29,300 --> 00:40:33,230
Bay harbor butcher is one of our own.

698
00:40:35,260 --> 00:40:37,960
We keep this to ourselves for now --

699
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,260
just the three of us.

700
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:42,200
I'm gonna go tell it to a bottle of scotch.

701
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:23,930
Here we are again.

702
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:27,330
What -- what the fuck?!

703
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:31,760
I know. I keep asking myself that same question.

704
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:41,930
Let me out of here!

705
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:43,330
But...

706
00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:47,960
I'm finding it's best to accept things you can't change,

707
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:49,260
you know?

708
00:41:49,300 --> 00:41:52,230
Normally,I'd have a chat

709
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:55,660
to make sure you understand why you're here,but...

710
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:59,900
I think you have a pretty good idea.

711
00:41:59,930 --> 00:42:02,200
Let me go.

712
00:42:02,230 --> 00:42:04,660
I got cocaine.

713
00:42:04,700 --> 00:42:07,000
You can have all of it.

714
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:11,800
It's funny you should say that. I am off the wagon.

715
00:42:11,830 --> 00:42:15,130
But that was never my drug.

716
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:19,300
I'll fucking kill you!

717
00:42:23,930 --> 00:42:25,330
No,mr. Jiminez.

718
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:29,360
I'm gonna kill you tonight...

719
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:32,600
For what you did to my mother...

720
00:42:32,630 --> 00:42:36,960
And because,well,this is what I do best.

721
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:47,800
It's kind of fitting,don't you think?

722
00:43:13,560 --> 00:43:16,660
Astor,cody,come on,let's eat.

723
00:43:19,830 --> 00:43:21,930
How'd you get the door unlocked?

724
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:24,600
It was already open.

725
00:43:24,630 --> 00:43:26,760
Oh,that's odd.

726
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:46,000
Starlight lanes 1690 michigan 7:00

727
00:44:46,800 --> 00:44:48,130
lila.

728
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:58,760
Hello?

729
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:00,200
Dexter,hi.

730
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:02,060
Um,look,I'm sorry to bother you,

731
00:45:02,100 --> 00:45:03,730
and I'm sure this is nothing,

732
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:06,700
but I was just wondering if by chance you were at my house.

733
00:45:06,730 --> 00:45:08,660
Uh,well,no.

734
00:45:08,700 --> 00:45:10,300
Well,it's just that the door was open

735
00:45:10,330 --> 00:45:12,860
and you're the only other one with a key.

736
00:45:16,900 --> 00:45:19,200
Rita,get out of the house. Call the police.

737
00:45:19,230 --> 00:45:21,360
I'll be there as soon as I can.

739
00:45:28,860 --> 00:45:32,160
I can't take you with me.

740
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:34,560
Don't go anywhere!

741
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:40,260
Oh,hey,I'm sorry to drag you into this.

742
00:45:40,300 --> 00:45:42,160
No,no,I'm glad you called. The kids?

743
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:43,800
Next door.

744
00:45:46,360 --> 00:45:49,630
The place is empty. No sign of forcible entry.

745
00:45:49,660 --> 00:45:52,900
I'm guessing you just forgot to lock the door.

746
00:45:52,930 --> 00:45:54,500
If you need anything else --

747
00:45:54,530 --> 00:45:55,730
no,no. You're not leaving.

748
00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:56,960
Sir?

749
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:58,600
Someone was in this house.

750
00:45:58,630 --> 00:46:00,630
I need you to stay here in the house

751
00:46:00,660 --> 00:46:02,060
until I tell you it's safe.

752
00:46:02,100 --> 00:46:04,560
Really? I need to do those things.

753
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:05,930
I'm with miami metro homicide.

754
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:07,400
I know you don't take orders from me,

755
00:46:07,430 --> 00:46:08,600
but if you'd like,

756
00:46:08,630 --> 00:46:10,260
I could get lieutenant laguerta on the phone.

757
00:46:10,300 --> 00:46:12,200
Or if you prefer to speak to captain matthews,

758
00:46:12,230 --> 00:46:13,560
I could arrange that,as well.

759
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:15,460
Dexter,what's going on?

760
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:17,930
Please,just stay here,okay?

761
00:46:19,460 --> 00:46:21,430
It's one thing to fuck with me

762
00:46:21,460 --> 00:46:25,830
another to fuck with my  ex-girlfriend who hates me.

763
00:46:25,860 --> 00:46:29,130
The lila experiment is officially over.

764
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:31,430
Dexter!

765
00:46:31,460 --> 00:46:33,760
Give me rita's key.

766
00:46:37,660 --> 00:46:40,760
Well,that's your fault,isn't it,Dexter?

767
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:44,260
You lied to me about working late,

768
00:46:44,300 --> 00:46:47,530
and I thought I might find you there.

769
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:50,660
Do not ever go to rita's house again.

770
00:46:50,700 --> 00:46:53,130
Do you understand?

771
00:46:53,160 --> 00:46:56,700
Do you understand?

772
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:01,460
Is this the monster that you keep telling me about?

773
00:47:01,500 --> 00:47:04,500
Trust me,when you meet the monster,you'll know.

774
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:10,660
You called jiminez.

775
00:47:10,700 --> 00:47:12,530
Yeah, I suppose I did.

776
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:15,100
Why?

777
00:47:15,130 --> 00:47:17,460
Why would you try to have me killed?

778
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:19,300
You weren't going to get killed.

779
00:47:19,330 --> 00:47:21,500
That's why I did it at the bowling alley,

780
00:47:21,530 --> 00:47:24,100
so all your police-officer friends would be there.

781
00:47:24,130 --> 00:47:27,030
What were you thinking?! Are you insane?!

782
00:47:27,060 --> 00:47:30,160
I was trying to bring us back together again!

783
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:34,360
You were pulling away,and...

784
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:39,530
Remember at the hotel after you faced jiminez?

785
00:47:39,560 --> 00:47:43,860
That -- that's what I wanted!

786
00:47:43,900 --> 00:47:47,400
To bring you back.

787
00:47:47,430 --> 00:47:51,360
So you called him?

788
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:54,500
Well,it worked,didn't it?

789
00:47:54,530 --> 00:47:57,560
Last night. You and I.

790
00:47:57,600 --> 00:48:00,160
You fell asleep in my arms.

791
00:48:04,060 --> 00:48:07,160
What?!

792
00:48:09,630 --> 00:48:11,200
You --

793
00:48:11,230 --> 00:48:16,730
you are more dangerous than my addiction will ever be.

794
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,360
That's saying a lot.

795
00:48:21,800 --> 00:48:25,000
Stay away from rita.

796
00:48:25,030 --> 00:48:28,760
Stay away from me.

797
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:31,200
Or what?

798
00:48:33,100 --> 00:48:35,530
Or you will see the monster.

